ALSO PRIMARILY DRIVEN BY THE EFFECT OF LOWER CRUDE OIL PRICES. THIS EFFECT DROVE THE $1.24 BILLION REDUCTION IN INTERNATIONAL INCOME TAX EXPENSE BETWEEN YEAR-OVER-YEAR PERIODS, FROM $1.83 BILLION IN 2015 TO $588 MILLION IN 2016. REFER ALSO TO THE DISCUSSION OF THE EFFECTIVE INCOME TAX RATE IN

