, ON A RETROSPECTIVE BASIS. THE STANDARD PROVIDES THAT ALL DEFERRED INCOME TAXES BE CLASSIFIED AS NONCURRENT ON THE CONSOLIDATED BALANCE SHEET. THE PRIOR REQUIREMENT WAS TO CLASSIFY MOST DEFERRED TAX ASSETS AND LIABILITIES BASED ON THE CLASSIFICATION OF THE UNDERLYING ASSET OR LIABILITY. THE DECEMBER 31, 2015, CONSOLIDATED BALANCE SHEET HAS BEEN RESTATED AND THE EFFECTS ARE REDUCTIONS OF

